    <div class="biography">
      <h2>Biography</h2>
      <p><strong>Dr. Avul Pakir Jainulabdeen Abdul Kalam</strong> was an Indian aerospace scientist and the 11th President of India (2002–2007). He played a key role in India's civilian space and military missile development efforts and was known as the "Missile Man of India." His work on the Agni and Prithvi missiles earned him national recognition.</p>
      <p>Dr. Kalam was a visionary and a beloved teacher who inspired millions through his books, speeches, and leadership. His autobiography *Wings of Fire* and books like *Ignited Minds* reflect his dream of a developed India. He remained active in education and innovation until his final moments, passing away while delivering a lecture to students in 2015.</p>
    </div>

